Finally, there are a number of extra prologues: for Eccles., the
                        unidentified: ‘Incipit quartus ordo eorum librorum qui in ueteri testament
                           ' (fol. 238va); Stegmüller, Stegmüller, Bibl. 495 as a second
                        prologue to Daniel (316ra); Stegmüller, Bibl. 510,1 to Joel (327ra);
                              Stegmüller, Bibl. 525 to Micah (322rb);
                              Stegmüller, Bibl. 527 to Nahum (334rb);
                              Stegmüller, Bibl. 530 and 529 to Habakkuk
                           (335va); the unidentified ‘Iosyam regem iude cuius ternporibus
                        sophonias ’ and Stegmüller, Bibl. 532 to Zeph. (336va);
                              Stegmüller, Bibl. 540
                        (338va)
                        and a prologue beginning as JEROME, in Zachariam 1.1, CC
                           76A:749/6 to Zech. (338va–39ra).
